text: I noticed the docs are up on the website: <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/methods/content/search-for-content>

Hi Guys, where can I found more information about this tool? I need know if it predictive search, Thank you for help!

lol <@U6XDD2SAW> I’m not trying to be a jerk, but look at the post above yours. also a little further up is a link to this <https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vRiHj28f1Ycg0iAW_EJC58ErHem0YADhaNJIkyZgkuyAikiYUSDI3x2BY-CSZykt59rWHzzg8P6lbUL/pub>

That is basically all of the documentation so far I think. Natively I don’t think there’s any predictive behavior built in, but it does work well, and with the foundation they provide you could build your own predictive search behavior, though I don’t think that’s a minor feat.
by predictive you mean visual completion of the search?
<@U6XDD2SAW> Predictive search isn't useful for most site search applications. It is better to show autocompleted results of pages since the domain is much smaller
I also don't think this works clientside... isn't the result a HubL rendering of the results
You can do it either way. there’s a javascript API

Bazing! I haven't fiddled with the search yet - I've built my own version a while back that rendered results (blog posts) on a page refresh and assumed this worked the same way (making my work obsolete)
